quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to print x's values from 1 to 5. Increment x's value using ++ operator.
[!raw!]
int x = 1;
{0} (x <= 5) {
  cout << x << endl;
  x{1};
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Using Increment or Decrement[/h1]

The increment or decrement operators can be used to change values in the loop.
[b]For example: [/b][code format="cpp" codeId="202"]int num = 1;
while (num < 6) {
  cout << "Number: " << num << endl;
  [b]num++;[/b]
}

/* Outputs
Number: 1
Number: 2
Number: 3
Number: 4
Number: 5
*/[/code]
[note]num++ is equivalent to num = num + 1.[/note]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to allow user to enter a value using cin and store it in the 'number' variable 5 times.
[!raw!]
int x = 1;
int number;
while ({0} <= 5) {
 {1} >> number;
 x++;
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Using a while Loop[/h1]

A loop can be used to obtain multiple inputs from the user.
Let's create a program that allows the user to enter a number 5 times, each time storing the input in a variable.[code format="cpp"]int num = 1;
[b]int number;[/b]

while (num <= 5) {
  [b]cin >> number;[/b]
  num++;
}[/code]
[note]The above code asks for user input 5 times, and each time saves the input in the number variable.[/note]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to enter five numbers from the user and print their sum. Store the sum in the variable named total.
[!raw!]
int x = 1;
int number;
int total = 0;
{0} (x <= 5) {
  cin >> number;
  {1} = total + number;
  x++;
}
cout << "Sum: " << {2} << endl;

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Using a while Loop [/h1]

Now let's modify our code to calculate the sum of the numbers the user has entered.[code format="cpp" codeId="939"]int num = 1;
int number;
int total = 0;

while (num <= 5) {
  cin >> number;
 [b] total += number;[/b]
  num++;
}
cout << total << endl;[/code]
The code above adds the number entered by the user to the [b]total [/b]variable with each loop iteration.
Once the loop stops executing, the value of [b]total [/b]is printed. This value is the sum of all of the numbers the user entered. 
[note]Note that the variable [b]total [/b]has an initial value of 0.[/note]
